Up for sale is a RARE Browning M2HB beltfeld 50 BMG caliber heavy machine gun built by the pro's at TNW Firearms. The gun is extra special! It is a *REAL* semi M2 and *NOT* the cheaper M3HB parts kit variant builds that are out there. The M2 features beautiful wood spade grips and charging handle. Firearm was freshly parkerized by TNW and the overall condition is 95%+ which is outstanding for a weapon of this type!

This firearm was purchased in person from TNW Firearms at Knob Creek, KY Machine Gun Shoot in the fall of 2013. TNW was reluctant to sell this particular model, but as a collector, I made them a good offer and took it home! M2 has only been used for parade displays mounted on a WWII era Jeep. Otherwise this beautiful firearm has been securely stored and is now being offered up for sale for the keystone of your collection!

This M2 uses a BATFE approved semi auto configuration. This allows this to be a normal Title I gun that only needs a normal background check and paperwork like any other rifle. Purchaser / Transferee must be 21 as per Federal law to purchase this firearm. No mounts or other accessories included, although with my experience I can assist you in finding a tripod, ground/vehicle mount, etc. I can also offer the firearm without the barrel and provide a discount of $300. I can provide you contact information on a man to purchase quality NOS M2 barrels for ~$600. For the buyer who needs this firearm shipped, not shipping the barrel saves a bundle.
